                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[If I Only Had $400 for a Work PC, Here’s What I’d Do]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/if-i-only-had-400-for-a-work-pc-heres-what-id-do/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/52844692712_16be54b0a6_o.jpg" length="269" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[laptops]]></category><category><![CDATA[pc building]]></category><category><![CDATA[Ajazz AK820]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            $400 can buy you plenty of productivity if you know where to look.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you need a new work computer and have a tight budget of only $400, it might seem like an impossible task. However, if you know where and how to spend your money, you can build a surprisingly capable workstation setup. Here’s what I’d do with that budget.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 21:01:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/if-i-only-had-400-for-a-work-pc-heres-what-id-do/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Linux ip Command: 7 Practical Usage Examples]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/uses-for-the-linux-ip-command/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jordan Gloor]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tux-the-linux-mascot-holding-an-ethernet-cable-with-networking-icons-around.png" length="602" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><category><![CDATA[Wi-Fi Routers]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cloud & Internet]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            You can do more than just check your IP address.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Ever wondered what <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/657911/how-to-use-the-ip-command-on-linux/" target="_blank">the Linux ip command</a> might be able to do for you? Maybe you're just getting into Linux terminal work or network management. Let me walk you through some basic examples of the ip command at work.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 21:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/uses-for-the-linux-ip-command/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Cross-Platform Play: A Gamer's Nightmare? Why I Avoid It]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/reasons-i-always-avoid-cross-platform-multiplayer/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_2455673583.jpg" length="297" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Gaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[mouse]]></category><category><![CDATA[Online Gaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Let's all just stay in our lanes.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I'm not much of an online multiplayer gamer, preferring to play single-player games, or sticking to local multiplayer with people I know.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 20:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/reasons-i-always-avoid-cross-platform-multiplayer/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Robot Sports: Humanoid Athletes Compete in Groundbreaking Games]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-next-favorite-athlete-may-be-a-robot/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aran Folsom]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/humanoid-robots-sprinting-on-a-blue-running-track-in-a-stadium-with-the-title-world-humanoid-robot-games-whrg-displayed-at-the-top.png" length="1954" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Cutting Edge]]></category><category><![CDATA[Robotics]]></category><category><![CDATA[ai]]></category><category><![CDATA[Sports]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            These humanoids are running, jumping, and dancing their way into the world of sports.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>This year marked the first-ever international sporting event to feature humanoid robots as athletes. These robots, with some help from the humans behind their creation, competed against each other in the World Humanoid Robot Games to showcase the athletic and practical abilities these machines possess.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 19:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/your-next-favorite-athlete-may-be-a-robot/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[6 Tips to Use Your iPhone One-Handed]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/tips-to-use-iphone-one-handed/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Yash Wate]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/tips-to-use-your-iphone-one-handed.jpg" length="404" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[ios]]></category><category><![CDATA[Productivity]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Finger gymnastics? Not anymore.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>As screens get bigger, using a phone one-handed has become challenging over the years. However, if you use an iPhone, you can take advantage of some built-in iOS features to make the experience more comfortable.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 19:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/tips-to-use-iphone-one-handed/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google Gemini Can Now Take Your Audio Files]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/google-gemini-can-now-take-your-audio-files/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/google-gemini.jpg" length="114" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Gemini]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Gemini is finally taking your audio files.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Google's Gemini has finally added the ability to upload and analyze audio files. This new feature takes your audio files, including common formats like MP3, M4A, and WAV, and can transcribe, summarize, and extract key details from the content.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 18:51:36 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/google-gemini-can-now-take-your-audio-files/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[uBlock Origin's New Update Changes Built-in Blocklists]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ublock-origin-1-66-update/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/ublock-origin.jpg" length="63" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Chrome]]></category><category><![CDATA[Firefox]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft Edge]]></category><category><![CDATA[opera]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Some important changes in uBlock Origin v1.66.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>uBlock Origin, the popular browser extension for blocking ads and trackers, just received another update. uBlock Origin version 1.66 adds new blocking options, removes some built-in lists, and makes a few other changes.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 18:47:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ublock-origin-1-66-update/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Getting Started With Boolean Logic in Python]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/beginners-guide-to-boolean-logic-in-python/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Zunaid Ali]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/python-gamification.png" length="731" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Programming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Python]]></category><category><![CDATA[Productivity]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Drawing the line between true and false.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Boolean logic is an essential part of mathematics, engineering, and programming. In most languages, there's a dedicated Boolean data type. When you're new to Python, Booleans may confuse you due to how they specifically work in this language. We'll explore the ins and outs of Boolean logic in Python.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 18:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/beginners-guide-to-boolean-logic-in-python/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Looking Back at 50 Years of BMW]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/bmw-50-years-in-north-america/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Brent vd Schyff]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/p90612122_lowres_2000-e39-m5-front-vi.jpg" length="562" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[BMW]]></category><category><![CDATA[Sports Cars]]></category><category><![CDATA[SUVs]]></category><description><![CDATA[
